We fit all time series models using the rstanarm R package44 by implementing Bayesian MCMC methods. For each model, we sampled four chains with 10,000 iterations each (5,000 iterations included as warmup) for subnational level models and 10,000 iterations each for national models. Convergence was evaluated by using the launch_shinystan function of the rstanarm R package44. We primarily assessed the convergence of our models using the Gelman-Rubin convergence statistic45 and deemed convergence adequate when \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
